 * Import and use in MDX files: <PollingCaveat />
 */
---

<aside class="starlight-aside starlight-aside--caution" aria-label="Polling Performance">
  <p class="starlight-aside__title" aria-hidden="true">
    <span class="starlight-aside__icon">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" width="16" height="16">
        <path d="M12 2L1 21h22L12 2zm0 3.99L19.53 19H4.47L12 5.99zM11 10v4h2v-4h-2zm0 6v2h2v-2h-2z"/>
      </svg>
    </span>
    Polling Performance
  </p>
  <section class="starlight-aside__content">
    <p>
      Both Blizzard and Penguin use polling to discover new files. For optimal performance, files should have <strong>lexicographically ordered names</strong> (e.g., timestamps or UUIDv7). This enables high watermark tracking, where only files newer than the last processed file are listed. Without lexicographical ordering, the entire directory (or partition) must be listed on every poll interval.
    </p>
  </section>
</aside>
